1. *Oliver* je omiljeno voće mnogih ljudi. (Olives are a favorite fruit of many people.)
2. Volim da dodam *oliver* u svoju salatu. (I like to add olives to my salad.)
3. *Oliveri* se koriste u pripremi mnogih mediteranskih jela. (Olives are used in the preparation of many Mediterranean dishes.)
4. Ovaj *oliverov* ulje je odlično za kuvanje. (This olive oil is great for cooking.)
5. Kupio sam novi komplet *olivera* za pripremu hrane. (I bought a new set of olive utensils for food preparation.)
6. Želim da kupim *olivere* za ukrašavanje mog vrta. (I want to buy olive trees to decorate my garden.)
7. *Oliverov* list se koristi za pripremu čaja. (Olive leaves are used to make tea.)
8. *Olivera* ima mnogo sorti koje se razlikuju po ukusu. (There are many varieties of olives that differ in taste.)
9. *Oliveri* su bogati vitaminom E. (Olives are rich in vitamin E.)
10. Moja omiljena vrsta *olivera* su kalamata. (My favorite type of olives are kalamata.)

Note: In Serbian, the word "oliver" (olive) can have different forms depending on its grammatical function in the sentence. For example, "oliver" can be in the nominative case as a subject (*Oliver* je omiljeno voće mnogih ljudi), in the accusative case as a direct object (Volim da dodam *oliver* u svoju salatu), or in the genitive case as a possessive (*Oliverov* ulje je odlično za kuvanje).